Redfish Validator failed with message:
```
ERROR - ProductionDate not defined in schema ComputerSystem.v1_19_0 (check version, spelling and casing)
ERROR - ProductionDate not defined in schema Chassis.v1_21_0 (check version, spelling and casing)
ERROR - ProductionDate not defined in schema Manager.v1_14_0 (check version, spelling and casing)
```
I don't see the ProductionDate in the ComputerSystem, Chassis, and Manager schema.
Does we need to work with DMTF first?

> I don't see the ProductionDate in the ComputerSystem, Chassis, and Manager schema.

Then why did you add it there?  Please limit your changes to only what the spec allows.
This block of code is copy pasted a lot.  Please wrap into a method and unit test it.
We're at the point where this block of code need deduplicated before anything more is added to it.  There are 8 instances where essentially identical code is called.  They need reduced.

I don't see ProductionDate in the latest Fabric Adapter schema 
https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/FabricAdapter.v1_5_3.json

I don't see ProductionDate for Fan. 
https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/Fan.v1_5_2.json
I see it for PowerSupplies.
Need to talk to the DMTF about adding first.

This will fail the Redfish Validator

I don't see it for Managers either 
https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/Manager.v1_19_1.json

This needs to pass the Redfish Validator, either by talking to the DMTF getting them to add it to System, Manager, Chassis, etc, then bumping those schemas or by removing it from those schemas that don't have it.

It would be a few months before DMTF would release the new schemas so I suggest breaking it up into 2 parts, schemas that have this property today and later can add it to other properties after Redfish adds it

Thanks Ed, Gunnar for your review.

I already run the Redfish Service Validator and don't see the issue. The reason why is that the `Board Manufacturer Date` doesn't exist in FRU on the PowerSupply of our system. 
```
FRU Device Description : DPS-2700AB-1 B (ID 12)

 Product Name          : DPS-2700AB-1 B

 Product Area Checksum : OK
```
That why Redfish Service Validator does not flag this.

I add it because there is ProductionDate in PowerSupply Schemas.

19991399

Hi @Ed,
Per Dbus interface, the BuildDate format either as YYYYMMDD or YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/master/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Inventory/Decorator/Asset.interface.yaml#L20. So I could say it's valid time.
I will add more debug to dateStringToEpoch function.

Thanks,

Hi @Ed,

After adds debug to `dateStringToEpoch` function, I see that this not handles the format for `YYYYMMDD` and `YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ` https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/redfish-core/src/utils/time_utils.cpp#L17

I have a fix for this likes that:
```
-    for (const char* format : std::to_array({"%FT%T%Ez", "%FT%TZ", "%FT%T"}))
+    for (const char* format : std::to_array({"%FT%T%Ez", "%FT%TZ", "%FT%T","%Y%m%d", "%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ"}))
```

Tested:

Test case 1:
The input ISO 8601 timestamp: 20230531T000000Z
The output Epoch timestamp: 1685491200

Test case 2:
The input ISO 8601 timestamp: 20230531
The output Epoch timestamp: 1685491200


After uses getDateTimeUint to convert it to a Redfish value, the ProductionDate will shows:
"ProductionDate": "2023-05-31T00:00:00+00:00"

Could I have a new PR to update the `dateStringToEpoch` function?
